        {
            "endOffset": 274388,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "se0060",
                    "title": "The entropy inequality and technical estimates"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "se0070",
            "sentence": "\u25a1",
            "startOffset": 274387,
            "title": "The evolution of moments"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 254174,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "br0110": {
                    "endOffset": 254128,
                    "startOffset": 254124
                },
                "br0150": {
                    "endOffset": 254100,
                    "startOffset": 254096
                }
            },
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "Similar questions for the non-linear space-homogeneous Boltzmann equation have also been considered in the literature, and we refer to [15] for an overview and to [11] for convergence results with soft potentials.",
            "startOffset": 253961,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 252727,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "On the other hand, a technical motivation for our results is that inequalities relating the logarithmic entropy to its production rate are interesting by themselves, and are helpful in the study of non-linear models involving a linear Boltzmann term.",
            "startOffset": 252477,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 297031,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0120",
            "sentence": "\u25a1",
            "startOffset": 297030,
            "title": "Stretched-exponential rate of convergence to equilibrium"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 266745,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "se0010",
                    "title": "Introduction"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "se0050",
            "sentence": "This will not only give an alternative to point (iii) (which will not improve the rate of convergence for Theorem 1.4), but will be crucial in the proof of Theorem 1.5, which we will give in Section 5.",
            "startOffset": 266544,
            "title": "Organization of the paper"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 259728,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "se0010",
                    "title": "Introduction"
                }
            ],
            "refoffsets": {
                "br0050": {
                    "endOffset": 259675,
                    "startOffset": 259672
                }
            },
            "secId": "se0030",
            "sentence": "In particular, we state the following theorem from [5], which will play an important role in our own study:",
            "startOffset": 259621,
            "title": "Known properties of the linear Boltzmann equation"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 252476,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "br0010": {
                    "endOffset": 252242,
                    "startOffset": 252239
                },
                "br0040": {
                    "endOffset": 252475,
                    "startOffset": 252466
                },
                "br0100": {
                    "endOffset": 252475,
                    "startOffset": 252466
                },
                "br0130": {
                    "endOffset": 252297,
                    "startOffset": 252280
                },
                "br0160": {
                    "endOffset": 252266,
                    "startOffset": 252262
                },
                "br0170": {
                    "endOffset": 252475,
                    "startOffset": 252466
                },
                "br0280": {
                    "endOffset": 252218,
                    "startOffset": 252211
                },
                "br0290": {
                    "endOffset": 252218,
                    "startOffset": 252211
                }
            },
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "Various versions of the linear Boltzmann equation are used to model phenomena such as neutron scattering [27,28], radiative transfer [1] and cometary flows [16] (we refer to [13, Chapter XXI] for a detailed presentation of the mathematical theory of linear collisional kinetic equations), and appears in some non-linear models as a background interaction term [4,10,17].",
            "startOffset": 252106,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 270269,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "se0060",
                    "title": "The entropy inequality and technical estimates"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "se0070",
            "sentence": "The study of moments and their time evolution is fundamental in many kinetic equations (and other PDEs where \u201cenergy methods\u201d are applicable).",
            "startOffset": 270127,
            "title": "The evolution of moments"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 256608,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "se0010",
                    "title": "Introduction"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "se0020",
            "sentence": "Before we present the main result of our work we recall in the next section a few known facts about the linear Boltzmann equation.",
            "startOffset": 256478,
            "title": "The linear Boltzmann operator"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 251641,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "We are interested in the application of entropy techniques to study the approach to equilibrium in the relative entropy sense, and in the application of entropy inequalities to estimate its rate.",
            "startOffset": 251446,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 254476,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "However, the question remains open regarding the validity of some functional inequalities in the non-cutoff case; we comment on this at the end of this introduction.",
            "startOffset": 254311,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 266943,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "se0010",
                    "title": "Introduction"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "se0050",
            "sentence": "In Section 6, we discuss the case of the linear Boltzmann equation with soft potential without the cut-off assumption and show the existence of a spectral gap for a certain range of the parameters.",
            "startOffset": 266746,
            "title": "Organization of the paper"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 279268,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "se0060",
                    "title": "The entropy inequality and technical estimates"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "se0090",
            "sentence": "We will then investigate the relation between the entropy and entropy production of it and the original solution.",
            "startOffset": 279155,
            "title": "Lower bounds \u2013 modification of the solution"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 257996,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "se0010",
                    "title": "Introduction"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "se0030",
            "sentence": "The first important observation in the study of the rate of convergence to equilibrium is the fact that linear Boltzmann equation (1.1) admits infinitely many Lyapunov functionals.",
            "startOffset": 257816,
            "title": "Known properties of the linear Boltzmann equation"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 252013,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "Our motivation comes partly from the study of the linear Boltzmann equation itself, which is a basic model in kinetic theory describing the collisional interaction of a set of particles with a thermal bath at a fixed temperature.",
            "startOffset": 251784,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 252899,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "br0050": {
                    "endOffset": 252790,
                    "startOffset": 252787
                }
            },
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "These inequalities are intriguing and have been studied in [5] in the case of hard potentials; we intend to complete these ideas by looking at the case of soft potentials.",
            "startOffset": 252728,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 267003,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "se0010",
                    "title": "Introduction"
                }
            ],
            "refoffsets": {
                "br0330": {
                    "endOffset": 267002,
                    "startOffset": 266998
                }
            },
            "secId": "se0050",
            "sentence": "This is done by an adaptation of similar results from [30].",
            "startOffset": 266944,
            "title": "Organization of the paper"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 251445,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "This work is concerned with the asymptotic behaviour of the linear homogeneous Boltzmann equation in the less explored case of soft potential interactions, and with a cut-off assumption (the precise definition of all the above will be given shortly).",
            "startOffset": 251195,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 295296,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0110",
            "sentence": "\u25a1",
            "startOffset": 295295,
            "title": "Instantaneous generation of Maxwellian lower bounds"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 259620,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "se0010",
                    "title": "Introduction"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "se0030",
            "sentence": "The study of the entropy method is more developed for the Maxwellian and hard potentials case.",
            "startOffset": 259526,
            "title": "Known properties of the linear Boltzmann equation"
        }
